The paper deals with the Node-Disjoint Paths (NDP) problem, which is a graph routing problem. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are likely categories. The problem is known to be NP-hard, so cs.NP (Computational Complexity) is also a likely category. The paper also discusses approximation algorithms, which suggests that cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) are also possible categories.
